# Supersymmetry.SUSYAlgebra

SUSY algebra anticommutators.

The N=1 super-Poincaré algebra in 4D adds supercharges Qα, Q̄α̇ to the Poincaré
algebra, with the key anticommutation relation:
  {Qα, Q̄β̇} = 2(σᵘ)_{αβ̇} Pᵘ

where Pᵘ is the 4-momentum generator and σᵘ are the Pauli 4-vectors.

The other anticommutators are:
  {Qα, Qβ} = 0,    {Q̄α̇, Q̄β̇} = 0

The connection to division algebras: in spacetime dimensions 3, 4, 6, 10 (associated
to ℝ, ℂ, ℍ, 𝕆), the SUSY algebra has a special form related to the normed division
algebra in that dimension. See Baez–Huerta arXiv:0909.0551.

Source: Wess and Bagger, "Supersymmetry and Supergravity" (1992), Chapter II.
Source: Baez and Huerta, "Division Algebras and Supersymmetry I", arXiv:0909.0551.

